Rape and incest is considered justifiable in Vanuatu and socioeconomic reasons can be grounds for consent for a woman to get an abortion. Under these guidelines, women’s ability to get an abortion should not be impeded by any person(s) publicly deprecating, arguing for, or against, the practice of abortion nor coercing a woman to an abortion by threats or force.

The Penal Code of Vanuatu makes abortion and miscarriage under any circumstances illegal. If the heads of a person who performs or self-administers first trimester, early second-trimester abortion perform, attempt so, be convicted the maximum penalty could be ten years imprisonment and or a fine of one hundred thousand Vatu ($100,000 VUV). A married woman may only lawfully obtain abortion with the permission of the woman’s husband. For an unmarried woman interposing with method is prescription twenty-four hours before an abortion occurs.

If a woman requests information regarding a surgical abortion, advocates will refer her to a clinic in Noumea, New Caledonia, or Australia and would contact an airplane taxi company to take her to Nadi International Airport, in Vanuatu’s neighbor Fiji.
